# PM Analyzer Tender Announcement
## Reference Number: cb-206-41600468
## Solicitation Number: 23-58169

The National Research Council Canada (NRC) is soliciting suppliers to submit a statement of capabilities for the procurement of a transient exhaust particle analyzer (hereafter referred to as the "Analyzer").

## Background
The NRC Energy, Mining and Environment (EME) division has a requirement to purchase a single (1) transient exhaust particle analyzer to measure the size distribution, number, and mass of particles in the exhaust gas of heavy-duty vehicles, engines, and equipment.

## Requirements
The proposed Analyzer must meet the following mandatory technical requirements:
- Test Method and Configuration: Include an integrated dilution and sampling system to allow direct measurement of particles in the exhaust flow immediately downstream of the exhaust manifold of an internal combustion engine or other locations in the exhaust piping of the engine without the use of a partial flow tunnel or constant volume sampler.
- Range of Measurement: Measure particle sizes between 5 to 2500 nm and raw particle number up to 1X10^11 particles/cubic cm.
- Necessary Accessories and Consumables: Include all necessary and non-standard accessories and consumables for operation of the Analyzer.
- Power supply Requirements: Include Canadian Standards Association approval and all power supplies, cables, and adapters to power the Analyzer through 120 V AC 60 Hz supply used in Canada.

## Criteria for Assessment of the Statement of Capabilities
Any interested supplier must demonstrate by way of a statement of capabilities that its system meets the requirements listed above.

## Contact Information
To obtain further information or to submit a statement of capabilities, please contact:
- Name: Jonathan Soles
- Title: Contracting Authority
- Telephone: 343-548-9258
- Email: Jonathan.Soles@nrc-cnrc.gc.ca

## Closing Date and Time
The closing date and time for accepting statements of capabilities is December 12th, 2023 at 14:00 hours Eastern Daylight Time (EDT).

## Tender Notice URL
Due to technical reasons, there is no link available for your reference.

## Notices Regarding the Trade Agreement(s)
The procurement is subject to the following trade agreement(s):
* Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership (CPTPP)
* Canada-European Union Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA)
* Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
* Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-Honduras Free Trade Agreement
* Canada
